
What is AIOPS and why AIOPS?

IT industry is dependent on SDLC
This SDLC gives us various model
Waterfall model
Agile mythology 
DevOps principles
AIOPS -> AI + OPS
Use of AI capabilities in the IT operations
AI ops is not just for IT industry- its for everyone
AIOPS : wherever in business that involves operations and automation using AI

Exisitng Automation Example:
Auto scaler :
CPU usage is 80%
Memory usage is 50% 
then scale up the VM
Here : we have set a rule -> and an action to take place (REACTION)

But now if AI is included with it: 
check the data based on the rule-> Observation Friday 5pm -> bring up 50 VM

Analyze the data based on the rule ->Proactively take the action

The major difference between DevOps and AI Ops: 
In DevOps we have automation 
AI ops we use algorithms, intelligence on given data and analyze and automate
AI is adding value to our IT operations.

AI : People, technology, process 
physical servers --> data centers -> VM -> Containers
With AI as people we learn new technologies and new process to improve ourselves.

3 main pillars of AIOPS:

- Data 
AIOps includes integrating with the Existing Systems to collect lots of data over a period of time
Observation and monitoring data on application
- Analytics : Difference between Analysis and Analytics?
Collecting data about your car? 
 - fuel?
 - engine?
 - battery?
 - tyre?
Analyze the data and come to a conclusion- take an action
Analytics : Analyze data based on previous actions, current actions and take necessary decisions even before the problem occurs
It is a continuous process
- Automation

Analytics pipleine:
====================
RAW data -->gets cleaned up -->Analyzed -> see it on the dashboard -> actions automatically 

Collection of RAW data is also called as Data Ingestion
===================
In the real time from the application the generated data is collected.
kafka
AWS kinesis

Example:
==============
Custome name, id, date, time, location, products, order

Data Storage 
========================
